### Image-to-Text (Captioning) with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Generate descriptive text captions for images. The pipeline can generate a single caption or multiple captions with customizable generation parameters like `max_new_tokens` and `temperature`.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Create image captioning pipeline
const captioner = await pipeline(
    'image-to-text',
    'Xenova/vit-gpt2-image-captioning'
);

// Generate caption
const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/beach.jpg';
const result = await captioner(url);
console.log(result);
// Output: [{ generated_text: 'a sandy beach with a blue ocean and palm trees' }]

// Generate multiple captions with sampling
const result2 = await captioner(url, {
    max_new_tokens: 50,
    num_beams: 5,
    num_return_sequences: 3,
    temperature: 1.2
});
console.log(result2);
// Output: [
//   { generated_text: 'a beautiful sandy beach with crystal clear blue water' },
//   { generated_text: 'a tropical beach with palm trees and white sand' },
//   { generated_text: 'a serene beach scene with turquoise ocean' }
// ]
```

