### Streaming Text Generation with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Stream generated text tokens in real-time using the Transformers.js library and a TextStreamer. This is useful for providing a better user experience by showing output as it's generated.

```javascript
import { pipeline, TextStreamer } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Create text generation pipeline
const generator = await pipeline(
    'text-generation',
    'onnx-community/Qwen2.5-Coder-0.5B-Instruct',
    { dtype: 'q4', device: 'webgpu' } // Example using webgpu
);

// Define chat messages
const messages = [
    { role: "system", content: "You are a helpful coding assistant." },
    { role: "user", content: "Write a quick sort algorithm in Python." }
];

// Create text streamer with callback
const streamer = new TextStreamer(generator.tokenizer, {
    skip_prompt: true,
    callback_function: (text) => {
        // This is called for each generated token
        process.stdout.write(text);  // Node.js example
        // or: document.getElementById('output').textContent += text;  // Browser example
    }
});

// Generate with streaming
const result = await generator(messages, {
    max_new_tokens: 512,
    do_sample: false,
    streamer
});

// Final result also available after streaming completes
console.log('\n\nFinal result:', result[0].generated_text);
// Output streams in real-time:
// Here's a simple implementation of the quick sort algorithm in Python:
//
// ```python
// def quick_sort(arr):
//     if len(arr) <= 1:
//         return arr
//     ...
// ```
```

