### Perform Text Processing with AutoTokenizer

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Illustrates direct usage of `AutoTokenizer` for custom text preprocessing. It covers encoding text into token IDs and attention masks, decoding token IDs back into text, performing batch encoding with padding and truncation, accessing the vocabulary, and converting between tokens and their corresponding IDs.

```javascript
import { AutoTokenizer } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Load tokenizer
const tokenizer = await AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained('Xenova/bert-base-uncased');

// Encode text
const text = 'Hello, world!';
const encoded = await tokenizer(text);
console.log(encoded);
// Output: { 
//   input_ids: Tensor [[101, 7592, 1010, 2088, 999, 102]],
//   attention_mask: Tensor [[1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1]]
// }

// Decode tokens
const decoded = tokenizer.decode(encoded.input_ids[0]);
console.log(decoded);
// Output: '[CLS] hello, world! [SEP]'

// Batch encoding
const texts = ['First sentence.', 'Second sentence.'];
const batchEncoded = await tokenizer(texts, {
    padding: true,
    truncation: true,
    max_length: 512
});
console.log(batchEncoded);
// Output: { 
//   input_ids: Tensor [[101, 2034, ...], [101, 2117, ...]],
//   attention_mask: Tensor [[1, 1, ...], [1, 1, ...]]
// }

// Get vocabulary
const vocab = tokenizer.model.vocab;
console.log(Object.keys(vocab).length); // 30522

// Convert tokens to IDs
const tokenIds = tokenizer.convert_tokens_to_ids(['hello', 'world']);
console.log(tokenIds); // [7592, 2088]

// Convert IDs to tokens
const tokens = tokenizer.convert_ids_to_tokens([7592, 2088]);
console.log(tokens); // ['hello', 'world']
```

