### JavaScript: Fill-Mask Task with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Predicts masked tokens in text for language modeling tasks using Transformers.js. It requires the `@huggingface/transformers` package and a fill-mask model. Input is text with one or more '[MASK]' tokens, and the output is a list of possible tokens and their probabilities.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Fill in masked words
const fillMask = await pipeline(
    'fill-mask',
    'Xenova/bert-base-uncased'
);

const result = await fillMask('The capital of France is [MASK].');
console.log(result);
// Output: [
//   { score: 0.9, token_str: 'paris', sequence: 'the capital of france is paris.' },
//   { score: 0.02, token_str: 'lyon', sequence: 'the capital of france is lyon.' },
//   { score: 0.01, token_str: 'marseille', sequence: 'the capital of france is marseille.' },
//   ...
// ]

// Multiple masks
const result2 = await fillMask('The [MASK] is the largest [MASK] in the solar system.');
console.log(result2);
// Output: [
//   { score: 0.75, token_str: 'sun', sequence: 'the sun is the largest star in the solar system.' },
//   { score: 0.15, token_str: 'jupiter', sequence: 'the jupiter is the largest planet in the solar system.' },
//   ...
// ]
```

