### JavaScript: Token Classification (NER) with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Identifies and classifies tokens in text for tasks like Named Entity Recognition (NER) using Transformers.js. It requires the `@huggingface/transformers` package and a pre-trained NER model. Input is text, and output is a list of identified entities with their scores and positions.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Token classification for Named Entity Recognition
const ner = await pipeline(
    'token-classification',
    'Xenova/bert-base-NER'
);

const result = await ner('My name is Sarah and I live in London');
console.log(result);
// Output: [
//   { entity: 'B-PER', score: 0.997, word: 'Sarah', start: 11, end: 16 },
//   { entity: 'B-LOC', score: 0.999, word: 'London', start: 31, end: 37 }
// ]

// Group entities together
const result2 = await ner('Apple Inc. was founded by Steve Jobs in California.', {
    aggregation_strategy: 'simple'
});
console.log(result2);
// Output: [
//   { entity_group: 'ORG', score: 0.998, word: 'Apple Inc.', start: 0, end: 10 },
//   { entity_group: 'PER', score: 0.999, word: 'Steve Jobs', start: 26, end: 36 },
//   { entity_group: 'LOC', score: 0.997, word: 'California', start: 40, end: 50 }
// ]
```

