### JavaScript: Text Classification using Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Performs text classification, including basic sentiment analysis and zero-shot classification, using the Transformers.js library. It requires the `@huggingface/transformers` package. Input is text, and output is a classification result with labels and scores.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Basic sentiment analysis
const sentiment = await pipeline('sentiment-analysis');
const result1 = await sentiment('This product exceeded my expectations!');
// Output: [{'label': 'POSITIVE', 'score': 0.9998}]

// Zero-shot classification (no training data needed)
const zeroShot = await pipeline(
    'zero-shot-classification',
    'Xenova/mobilebert-uncased-mnli'
);

const result2 = await zeroShot(
    'I have a problem with my iphone that needs to be resolved asap!',
    ['urgent', 'not urgent', 'phone', 'tablet', 'computer']
);
console.log(result2);
// Output: {
//   sequence: 'I have a problem with my iphone that needs to be resolved asap!',
//   labels: ['urgent', 'phone', 'computer', 'tablet', 'not urgent'],
//   scores: [0.503, 0.479, 0.013, 0.003, 0.002]
// }
```

