### Text Translation with Transformers.js

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Translate text between languages using the Transformers.js library. This example demonstrates using a multilingual model and single-pair translation models.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Multilingual translation model
const translator = await pipeline('translation', 'Xenova/nllb-200-distilled-600M');

// Translate English to Greek
const result1 = await translator('I like to walk my dog.', {
    src_lang: 'eng_Latn',
    tgt_lang: 'ell_Grek'
});
console.log(result1);
// Output: [{ translation_text: 'Μου αρέσει να περπατάω το σκυλί μου.' }]

// Translate Greek back to English
const result2 = await translator(result1[0].translation_text, {
    src_lang: 'ell_Grek',
    tgt_lang: 'eng_Latn'
});
console.log(result2);
// Output: [{ translation_text: 'I like to walk my dog.' }]

// Single-pair translation models (often more accurate)
const enToFr = await pipeline('translation_en_to_fr', 'Xenova/t5-small');
const result3 = await enToFr('Hello, how are you?');
console.log(result3);
// Output: [{ translation_text: 'Bonjour, comment allez-vous?' }]
```
